title: After delay, Minneapolis schedules Downtown East Commons meeting
text:
Home / Brief / After delay, Minneapolis schedules Downtown East Commons meeting After delay, Minneapolis schedules Downtown East Commons meeting By: Karlee Weinmann September 30, 2015 12:06 pm 0 Minneapolis officials will hold a fourth public meeting to discuss a 4.2-acre downtown park on Oct. 14, three months behind their original schedule. The gathering will focus on a fine-tuned design for Downtown East Commons, the $22 million park project at the center of a broader revitalization of the Downtown East neighborhood.
